HAZYVIEW – Kruger National Park (KNP) and SANParks spokesman Ike Phaahla confirmed that there had been a break-in last night in the reception area of Numbi Gate. Phaahla assured the public the gate was open for tourists today. “This happened when the gate was closed last night so no tourists were affected. We can assure  our visitors to the KNP that their safety is our top priority.”